HEADWORD: off-key
<hw>off-key</hw> <pos>adj. & adv.</pos> <def>Deviating from the proper
pitch; -- of a musical note or series of notes; <as>as, an
<ex>off-key</ex> note; to sing <ex>off-key</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> false, sour.</syn>⟦br⟧
